## Implementation status

Tracks the 9 steps in §15 "Implementation Sequence":

| Step | Component | Status |
|------|-----------|--------|
| 1 | Postgres schema + frameworks/ | ✅ SQL ready; frameworks populated |
| 2 | Session runner | ⏳ not built |
| 3 | Extractor (Stage 01) | ⏳ not built |
| 4 | One phase worker (Stage 02 pilot) | ⏳ not built |
| 5 | Phase graph scheduler | ⏳ not built |
| 6 | Assembler (Stage 03) | ⏳ not built |
| 7 | Batch runner (CLI) | ⏳ not built |
| 8 | Observability | ⏳ not built |
| 9 | Post-hoc validator | ⏳ not built |

---

## Frameworks coverage

- **Subjects with frameworks (14 of 32):** Matematika, Algebra, Algebra_va_Analiz, Geometriya, Geometriya_Advanced, Biology, Chemistry, Physics, English, Ona_Tili, Rus_Tili, Tarix, Jahon_Tarixi, Ozbekiston_Tarixi.
- **Missing (18):** Astronomy, Geography, Combined Science, Literature, German, Law, Economy, Entrepreneurship, Civic Prep, Ancient History, and the 9 Tarbiya/Sanat subjects. Add by creating `frameworks/subjects/{name}.md` following the existing pattern.

---

## What the pipeline does NOT use

Per §16: no LangChain, LangGraph, CrewAI, n8n, agent orchestrators, or RAG indices. This is ~600 lines of Python against a Postgres queue. That's the feature.
